\f0\b \cf5 \strokec5 3 
\f1\b0 However, when the people of Gibeon heard what Joshua had done to Jericho and Ai, 
\f0\b 4 
\f1\b0 they resorted to a ruse:\cf2 \strokec2 \
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Gibeonites joined the people of God\uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What I want you to see is that when God moves there are two responses from people - to reject you or join you.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What we see are the people of Gibeon joining the people of Israel.\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
